	order_index: 4
	quest_links: [ ]
	quests: [
		{
			description: [
				"Welcome to ComputerCraft! Here you will be building and programming computers using Lua, a real life language, renowned for being beginner-friendly."
				""
				"On its own, the &3basic computer&r is little more than an advanced logic gate and item sorter, but that changes quickly through the use of peripherals! This chapter will point out what you can do with this newfangled technology."
				""
				"Since Lua is a coding language used in real life, you can look up any tutorial you wish to get familiar with its concepts! "
				"For more info on ComputerCraft in particular, the images of books in this chapter to links to wikis."
			]
			id: "5F2D9F4908401D0D"
			subtitle: "You've met Luna. Prepare for Lua"
			tasks: [{
				id: "2E906826F6FDAF5F"
				item: "computercraft:computer_normal"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Welcome to ComputerCraft!"
			x: -6.0d
			y: 3.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5F2D9F4908401D0D"]
			description: [
				"These function almost identical to their basic counterparts but..."
				"- &3Computers,&r &3pocket computers&r, and &3turtles&r can run multiple programs at once using the \"&dmultishell&r\" library"
				"- &3Turtles&r have a bigger fuel tank"
				"- All 4 support color! &cW&6o&ew&ai&9e&d!"
			]
			id: "791B05ACA5FD85FC"
			subtitle: "Better than ever!"
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "065C2D0A373063AB"
					item: "computercraft:computer_advanced"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "6694EF08DED64B71"
					item: "computercraft:turtle_advanced"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "6BEF24FE2926ACF0"
					item: "computercraft:pocket_computer_advanced"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "6F32EA6613583DD1"
					item: "computercraft:monitor_advanced"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			title: "Advanced Variants"
			x: -5.0d
			y: 1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5F2D9F4908401D0D"]
			description: [
				"A portable computer than can be used from your hotbar or offhand! "
				"It only has 1 slot for peripherals, accessed from the \"back\", but you can use the \"&eequip()&r\" and \"&eunequip()&r\" functions from the \"&dpocket&r\" library if you're feeling clever."
				""
				"Holding in your offhand renders the terminal like a &3vanilla map&r."
			]
			id: "4CD956A0E923C1B6"
			subtitle: "Ipad Baby"
			tasks: [{
				id: "74F8BAFCA9F2881B"
				item: "computercraft:pocket_computer_normal"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: -7.0d
			y: 1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5F2D9F4908401D0D"]
			description: [
				"&3Turtles&r are computers that can move, mine, build, fight, pick up items, and see! They are incredibly powerful, especially since they have 2 slots for peripherals, accessed on the \"left\" and \"right\" sides."
				""
				"&3Turtles&r can move forward, backward, up, and down at the cost of furnace fuel, and can turn left and right for free."
				""
				"Their ability to place blocks also gives them a limited ability to simulate right clicks. It's rather inconsistent, but don't let that stop you from experimenting!"
				""
				"You can give them a nametag with \"&dos.&esetComputerLabel()&r\", or even color them with dye in a crafting table!"
			]
			hide_dependent_lines: true
			id: "3C6A84E06D46CD0F"
			subtitle: "Asimov would be concerned"
			tasks: [{
				id: "5E8B93E5E8506DEF"
				item: "computercraft:turtle_normal"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: -6.0d
			y: 1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["160EC57392A6C5D5"]
			description: [
				"Monitors are used to display text and symbols! "
				""
				"It uses a \"cursor\" system that's hidden by default. You can use \"&esetCursorBlink()&r\" to reveal it, and use \"&esetCursorPos()&r\" from the \"&dmonitor&r\" library to move it! The top-left corner of the screen is defined as (1, 1)."
				""
				"You can also use it as a touch screen using the \"&9monitor_touch&r\" event, and you can draw a pixel by setting the background color of your text, then writing an empty space."
				""
				"They can be connected together to form pretty much any size rectangle you'd like!"
			]
			id: "0B29A2BF94C63336"
			subtitle: "Look ma! I'm on TV!"
			tasks: [{
				id: "616B08AEEACAD536"
				item: "computercraft:monitor_normal"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: -1.0d
			y: 1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["160EC57392A6C5D5"]
			description: [
				"It's a &3speaker&r! What more could you want?"
				"It can plany any noteblock sound at any pitch, and play most game sounds."
				""
				"And if you're willing to go down a rabbit hole and learn about audio sampling and such, you can use it to play completely custom music and sounds."
			]
			id: "1BBFCD620C85DB80"
			subtitle: " Flutes and trombones and saxes from beyond"
			tasks: [{
				id: "7DD0AB6A9A957F8B"
				item: "computercraft:speaker"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 0.0d
			y: 1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["160EC57392A6C5D5"]
			description: [
				"&3Drisk drives&r and &3floppy disks&r serve as both an auxilary storage for data, as well as a way to automatically copy data to new computers. If you wanna make a self-replicating &3turtle&r army, you'll need these!"
				""
				"&3Floppy disks&r can hold up to 125 kilobytes of data each."
			]
			id: "5B1A8D8CC62FC5B1"
			subtitle: "Why is the save icon a vending machine?"
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "09F3121204F7195A"
					item: "computercraft:disk_drive"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "2691C1EABAAF0305"
					item: {
						Count: 1
						id: "ftbfiltersystem:smart_filter"
						tag: {
							"ftbfiltersystem:filter": "ftbfiltersystem:item_tag(computercraft:disks)"
						}
					}
					title: "Any #computercraft:disks"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			x: 1.0d
			y: 1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["160EC57392A6C5D5"]
			description: [
				"Yeah! &3Computers&r can be wrapped as peripherals by other &3computers&r!"
				""
				"You can't do that much though. You can just get the ID and label, and turn it on and off."
			]
			id: "21EAABD0D38C744D"
			subtitle: "How recursive!"
			tasks: [{
				id: "3079507A3939B9C7"
				item: {
					Count: 1
					id: "ftbfiltersystem:smart_filter"
					tag: {
						"ftbfiltersystem:filter": "or(item(computercraft:computer_normal)item(computercraft:computer_advanced))"
					}
				}
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Computers"
			x: -1.0d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["160EC57392A6C5D5"]
			description: [
				"&3Wireless&r and &3ender modems&r are essentially upgraded &3redstone links&r, able to transmit data over long distances, and tell how far apart computers are."
				""
				"&3Wireless modems&r have a limited range that gets longer the higher up in the world its placed. The range is reduced while raining though."
				""
				"&3Ender modems&r have unlimited range and can even transmit data across dimensions, making it very useful for interplanetary logistics."
				""
				"You can use either the \"&drednet&r\" or \"&dmodem&r\" library for sending messages. &dRednet&r is much easier to set up at the cost of finer control, and &dmodem&r is the opposite."
				""
				"You can transmit any kind of data except for functions and metatables."
				"This is a good thing."
			]
			id: "029B6ECECAE729D8"
			subtitle: "RCE Machines"
			tasks: [{
				id: "681E084FFAE1538B"
				item: {
					Count: 1
					id: "ftbfiltersystem:smart_filter"
					tag: {
						"ftbfiltersystem:filter": "or(item(computercraft:wireless_modem_normal)item(computercraft:wireless_modem_advanced))"
					}
				}
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Wireless and Ender Modems"
			x: 0.0d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["160EC57392A6C5D5"]
			description: [
				"&3Wired modems&r allow you expand the number of peripherals a &3computer&r can connect to! No longer are you limited to 6 faces!"
				""
				"Using these, it's only natural you try to make some kind of AE2-like system, since you can use it to wrap &3inventories&r and &3fluid tanks&r as peripherals and move your things about the place."
				""
				"Oh yeah, and it can do everything &3wireless&r and &3ender modems&r can do, but only on the wired network its connected to."
			]
			id: "47D9E37D0E20B6F5"
			subtitle: "AE2 is crying in the corner"
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "340F93D39415017C"
					item: "computercraft:wired_modem"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "77520C95616AC4DF"
					item: "computercraft:cable"
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			x: 1.0d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["160EC57392A6C5D5"]
			description: [
				"It prints text onto &3paper&r! You can set the color of the text by inserting dye items, and you need to manually start and eject pages with the \"&enewPage()&r\" and \"&eendPage()&r\" functions."
				""
				"You can also use &3string&r or &3yarn&r to bind the printed pages into a pamplet, or add &3leather&r to the mix to make a book!"
			]
			id: "7DC9A7FA540C670C"
			subtitle: "No laser printers"
			tasks: [{
				id: "277E212F93FC34B5"
				item: "computercraft:printer"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: -1.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["160EC57392A6C5D5"]
			description: ["This one just extends the \"&dredstone&r\" library, allowing you to set and get signals by this block as if it was a whole computer!"]
			id: "08C8C4E751DF5CBA"
			subtitle: "When 6 faces aren't enough"
			tasks: [{
				id: "754E959DC88029F6"
				item: "computercraft:redstone_relay"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 0.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["3058785E70954678"]
			description: [
				"The &3Environment Detector&r is a versitile peripheral! Almost like the mod author crammed a bunch of random features into it because they didn't fit anywhere else."
				""
				"This thing can read various stats about the local light level, the biome and dimension its in, the phase of the moon, the current weather, the time of day, and the nearby entities."
				""
				"If you haven't solved animal hubsandry yet, this should help a bit, as it can count animals and read a specific animal's gender, in a roundabout way!"
				""
				"Also the phase of the moon can be used to determine the day of the month."
			]
			id: "366B73FA1A626DBD"
			subtitle: "Climate Science??? In MY GregTech?!"
			tasks: [{
				id: "7FEE9F7879B91E48"
				item: "advancedperipherals:environment_detector"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 2.5d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["3058785E70954678"]
			description: [
				"The Chat Box can be used to send and recieve chat messages! How about it! "
				"It can send messages to specific players, and format them with &cc&6o&el&ao&br&ds&f, &lbolding,&r &oitalics,&r &1&nlinks&r&r, the usual!"
				""
				"It can even send toasts - the things that pop up on the top right of your screen when you complete a quest."
			]
			id: "780995E2158D5314"
			subtitle: "Apocolyptic amounts of yapping"
			tasks: [{
				id: "597B5BD38B0AF794"
				item: "advancedperipherals:chat_box"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 3.5d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["3058785E70954678"]
			description: [
				"The &3Player Detector&r is a block that can read a list of people currently logged in, as well as a bit of information of each."
				""
				"What kind of information? Well, their..."
				"- Current and max health"
				"- Air supply"
				"- Current dimension"
				"- Direction"
				"- Spawn point"
				"- Current position"
				"You know, the usual things."
			]
			id: "2421D1ADA60C3BB3"
			subtitle: "Stalkers' best friend"
			tasks: [{
				id: "56CA2DC49B25B0BA"
				item: "advancedperipherals:player_detector"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 4.5d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["3058785E70954678"]
			description: [
				"The &3ME bridge&r allows your computers to interface with your &2AE2&r systems, allowing it to view various stats, order crafts on your &3CPUs&r, or just push and pull items to and from the systems. "
				""
				"You can use this to, for example, emulate a &3ME requester&r in &6HV&r instead of &5EV.&r You could emulate a hundred &3ME requesters&r, for that matter!"
				""
				"It consumes a channel, by the way."
			]
			id: "01950B026EAAECE2"
			subtitle: "Digital logic meets digital storage"
			tasks: [{
				id: "6C0E708A4AC5812A"
				item: "advancedperipherals:me_bridge"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 2.5d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["3058785E70954678"]
			description: [
				"The &3Inventory Manager&r is a block that lets you interface with player inventories, accessing their hotbar, inventory, offhand, and armor. You could even push or pull items from the inventory to surrounding storage blocks."
				""
				"In order to use it, you need to bind a &3memory card&r to yourself, which can be done with a shift-right click. The card can then be inserted into the &3manager&r block."
				""
				"It should go without saying, but don't give your memory card to someone you don't trust. Failing to do so could utterly &cruin&r you."
			]
			id: "562C44506B8D6B5B"
			subtitle: "Step 1 of getting softlocked"
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "5926DDE12F4A3C9F"
					item: "advancedperipherals:inventory_manager"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "3FAE91F369EAEB3D"
					item: {
						Count: 1
						id: "advancedperipherals:memory_card"
						tag: { }
					}
					type: "item"
				}
			]
			x: 3.5d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["3058785E70954678"]
			description: [
				"The &3Block Reader&r reads the data of the block it's pointing at! This includes the block itself and its NBT data."
				""
				"There all sorts of nonsense you can get up to with this thing. For example, you could... "
				""
				"1. Use a &3schematic canon&r to make a list of materials in a &3book and quil&r"
				"2. Put the &3book and quil&r in a &3lecturn&r"
				"3. Have the &3block reader&r read the &3book&r in the &3lecturn&r"
				"4. Pass that data to an &3ME bridge&r to craft all the stuff in the schematic"
				""
				"It's a lot of work, but the results are so satisfying~"
			]
			id: "4DE6ED0D9603524C"
			subtitle: "Smartest Observer"
			tasks: [{
				id: "255D175973D44694"
				item: "advancedperipherals:block_reader"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 4.5d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["3058785E70954678"]
			description: [
				"The NBT storage&3 lets you store data in the NBT data of the block!"
				""
				"This is very useful if you don't want to futz about with Lua's file IO system, especially since it can hold 1 megabyte of data, and it's resistant to chunk unloads and server restarts."
				""
				"It's not a perfect solution though, since they can't be carried by &3turtles&r."
			]
			id: "5F5865233C224165"
			subtitle: "The start of a datacenter"
			tasks: [{
				id: "3DA1EA7E49A65DDE"
				item: "advancedperipherals:nbt_storage"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 2.5d
			y: 1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: [
				"3058785E70954678"
				"3C6A84E06D46CD0F"
			]
			description: [
				"The Weak Automata Core - and all other cores - massively extend the functionality of a &3turtle&r drone."
				""
				"It allows them to scan nearby items and entities, selectively pick up items, refuel using batteries that store RF (not EU), and simulate right clicks way better."
				""
				"Most of these abilities have a cooldown AND a fuel cost, but you can increase one to lower the other, to better suit your needs. "
			]
			hide_dependent_lines: true
			id: "191EEC093AC4E4D4"
			subtitle: "This should just be in the base mod."
			tasks: [{
				id: "546F1E11F9556CE6"
				item: {
					Count: 1
					id: "advancedperipherals:weak_automata_core"
					tag: { }
				}
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 2.5d
			y: -2.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: [
				"3058785E70954678"
				"3C6A84E06D46CD0F"
			]
			description: [
				"The &3Husbandy Automata&r core can do everything the &3Weak Automata Core&r can do, and more!"
				""
				"It can simulate right clicks on animals, gather the same info on animals that an&3 Environmental Detector&r can get, and capture an animal for release elsewhere."
				""
				"You DEFINITELY should have automated animals at this point. You got this before going to Mars, right?"
			]
			hide_dependent_lines: true
			id: "44948F5DD2BA92E6"
			subtitle: "Cow tipping and kidnapping"
			tasks: [{
				id: "066FB2E7EB270C86"
				item: "advancedperipherals:husbandry_automata_core"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 3.5d
			y: -2.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: [
				"3058785E70954678"
				"3C6A84E06D46CD0F"
			]
			description: [
				"The &3Ender Automata&r core can do everything the &3Weak Automata Core&r can do, and more!"
				""
				"This core's theme is teleportation! It allows the turtle to record its current position, and teleport back to it at the cost of fuel! Unfortunately, these points can't be manipulated with code."
				""
				"Removing the core permanently removes all the saved points, so be careful!"
			]
			hide_dependent_lines: true
			id: "30AC05ADD73C548C"
			subtitle: "There and back in an instant"
			tasks: [{
				id: "10CC3F9AA5628EAB"
				item: "advancedperipherals:end_automata_core"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 4.5d
			y: -2.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["3058785E70954678"]
			description: [
				"The &3Geoscanner&r scans the nearby enviornment, printing out the data in a ridiculously large &9table.&r There is a cooldown however, and a longer-ranged scan increases said cooldown."
				""
				"If you're truly sick of ore prospecting, you can slap this bad boy on your &3pocket computer&r and frolic through the countryside for a while, the ipad recording anything of note as you go."
			]
			id: "1F08650436F72A14"
			subtitle: "Halfway to a digital miner"
			tasks: [{
				id: "1E5F565820EC3D9F"
				item: "advancedperipherals:geo_scanner"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 3.5d
			y: 1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["6226DDF4F16D439B"]
			description: [
				"A candidate for the most useless peripheral. "
				"&eextend()&r - forces the sticky side to extend."
				"&eretract()&r - forces the sticky side to retract."
				"&etoggle()&r - toggles between the two states."
				""
				"Wow."
			]
			id: "4C206263E6B050FD"
			subtitle: "Why though?"
			tasks: [{
				id: "3460D536419CE199"
				item: "create:sticker"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 6.0d
			y: 1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["6226DDF4F16D439B"]
			description: [
				"As a peripheral, you can set the text and color of the tubes with code! Great for animated signs without &3deployer&r jank!"
				""
				"&esetText(&astring &9Text&e)&r - Sets what text is displayed on the tubes"
				"&esetColor(&astring &9Color&e)&r - Sets the color of the text"
			]
			id: "27B1F8D84A175533"
			subtitle: "Classier Signs"
			tasks: [{
				id: "48456E48BD67DFFB"
				item: "create:nixie_tube"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 7.0d
			y: 0.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["6226DDF4F16D439B"]
			description: [
				"The &3speedometer&r and &3stressometer&r only have a few functions."
				""
				"&3Speedometer&r:"
				"&egetSpeed()&r - returns the speed in RPM."
				""
				"&3Stressometer&r:"
				"&egetStress()&r - returns how much SU is currently being used."
